act:act.act:title: Trade, Investment and Labour Mobility Agreement Implementation Act

bcl:text.#text: In this Act,  means the Trade, Investment and Labour Mobility Agreement entered into by the governments of British Columbia and Alberta on April 28, 2006 and includes amendments to the Agreement.

bcl:section.bcl:marginalnote: Prohibition on private cause of action

bcl:subsection.bcl:text: Subject to subsection (2), no legal proceeding lies or may be brought or continued against the government or another person to enforce or determine a right or obligation that is claimed or arises solely under the Agreement or the Agreement as interpreted by a joint decision issued under Article 34 (4) of the Agreement.
Subsection (1) does not apply to a proceeding that is contemplated by Part IV of the Agreement.

No legal proceeding lies or may be brought or continued against the government for compensation, damages or any other remedy for anything arising as a consequence of a joint decision issued under Article 34 (4) of the Agreement.

bcl:section.bcl:text: The Lieutenant Governor in Council by order may assign to the minister the responsibility of

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text: carrying out on behalf of the government any of its powers or duties under the Agreement, or
exercising on behalf of the government any discretion it has under the Agreement.

bcl:text.#text: An application of a person for enrolment as a member under the , R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 334, that was commenced before the coming into force of this section and the amendments made by this Act to sections 5, 6 and 11 of the  is deemed to be an application for enrolment without a limitation on the member's practice relating to a notarial district or area.

The practice of a member who was enrolled under section 11 of the , R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 334, as it read immediately before the coming into force of this section and amendments made by this Act to section 11 of the , is deemed not to be limited to the notarial district or area recorded by the registrar on the roll.

An appointment made under section 15 (1) (a) of the , R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 334, as it read immediately before the coming into force of this section and amendments made by this Act to section 15 of the , remains in force in accordance with its terms until the appointment expires, is rescinded or amended or another is made in its place.
